What is AWS Cloud? 
AWS is the world's most widely adopted cloud computing platform, providing online access to computing resources, storage, databases, and other it services.

Launched in 2006 with Simple Storage Service(s3), AWS pioneered the cloud industry and now offers hundreds of services covering compute, storage, databases, machine learning and more..

