Benefits of cloud computing
Cloud computing offers benefits like cost savings, security, scalability and flexibility.
AWS highlights these six key benefits of cloud computing
1. Pay only for what you use
No upfront investment in data centers or servers. Start using services immediately scale as you grow and pay only for what you consume.
2. Benefit from Massive Economies of Scale
Sharing infrastructure with hundreds of thousands of customers lowers costs for everyone, giving businesses of all sizes access to advanced technologies at lower rates.
3. Stop Guessing Capacity
No more unused servers or capacity limits. Scale freely based on actual demand and pay only for what you use.
4. Increase speed and Agility
Provision resources in minutes instead of weeks. This flexibility let you experiment, innovate and iterate faster.
5. Stop Spending Money Running Data Centers
Eliminate the overhead of managing physical infrastructure and focus on your applications and customers instead.
6. Go Global in Minutes
Deploy applications worldwide using AWS data centers across the globe. Select regions close to your users for low latency and better performance.

