AWS Global Infrastructure — Simple Words Mein
Regions and Availability Zones
Socho AWS ke pass duniya bhar mein bahut bade-bade locations hain — yeh Regions hain (jaise Mumbai, Singapore, Virginia).
Har Region ke andar multiple data centers hote hain jinhe Availability Zones (AZ) kehte hain. Yeh sab ek dusre se alag (isolated) hote hain — apna power, apna networking.
Kyun important hai?

Agar ek data center mein problem ho jaaye (power cut, fire, etc.) toh dusra AZ apna kaam continue rakhta hai — tumhara application band nahi hota. Isi ko kehte hain High Availability aur Fault Tolerance.
Easy Example: Jaise tumhara ghar Delhi mein hai (Region), aur Delhi mein 3 alag societies hain jaha tumne apna data rakha hai (3 AZs). Agar ek society mein bijli chali jaaye, dusri 2 societies se kaam chalta rahega.

